text: Putnam County is a county in the U.S. state of Florida. It was formed on January 18, 1849. As of 2020, 73,321 people lived there. Putnam County's seat is Palatka. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official county website Category:Florida counties Category:1849 establishments in the United States Category:1840s establishments in Florida
